# Firebase Configuration
# Rename this file to .env.local and fill in your values from Firebase Console

NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_API_KEY=your-api-key-here
NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=your-project-id.firebaseapp.com
NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=your-project-id
NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=your-project-id.appspot.com
NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=your-sender-id
NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_APP_ID=your-app-id

# Instructions:
# 1. Go to Firebase Console > Project Settings > General
# 2. Scroll down to "Your apps" section
# 3. Copy the config values from there
# 4. Rename this file to .env.local (remove the .example part)
# 5. Restart your Next.js development server after saving

# IMPORTANT: Make sure the STORAGE_BUCKET value is correct and exists in Firebase
# If you get permission errors, check that:
#  1. Firebase Storage is initialized in your project
#  2. The rules in Firebase Storage allow read/write operations
#  3. Your project has billing enabled (may be required for some features)
